injuries.longComment: Davis missed all of last season due to a torn ACL, but he's now expected to be cleared by the start of training camp, and potentially even earlier. The 2020 sixth-round pick is a core special-teams contributor for Green Bay.
injuries.shortComment: The Packers are in line to re-sign Davis, Rob Demovsky of ESPN.com reports.

injuries.longComment: Dillon saw action in Green Bay's first 14 games of the season, but a pair of injuries prevented him from playing in two of the team's last four regular-season games as well as both of its postseason contests. Dillon will be a free agent this offseason, and the Packers could try to bring him back. However, after Dillon averaged 5.3 YPC as a rookie, that number dipped each of the last three seasons and bottomed out at 3.4 in 2023; consequently, the team could well opt to go in a different direction.
injuries.shortComment: Dillon (thumb/neck) tallied 178 carries for 613 yards and two touchdowns while adding 22 receptions for 223 yards over 15 games in the 2023 season.

injuries.longComment: Enagbare thought after he picked up the injury that it might be a bone bruise, but that turned out to be wishful thinking. He'll undergo surgery to repair his knee, and his availability for the start of the 2024 season now is in doubt.
injuries.shortComment: Enagbare sustained a torn ACL during the Packers' wild-card win at Dallas, Ryan Wood of USA Today reports.

injuries.longComment: Tom suffered a head injury in the second half and was subsequently evaluated for a concussion. He's since been deemed out for the remainder of the matchup. Yosh Nijman has taken over at right tackle in Tom's absence.
injuries.shortComment: Tom (concussion) won't return to Saturday's game versus San Francisco, Matt Schneidman of The Athletic reports.
